WEBVTT

00:00:00.166 --> 00:00:03.200
understand how signature based antivirus work first

00:00:03.200 --> 00:00:05.080
antivirus software usually

00:00:05.080 --> 00:00:07.133
detects malware by recognising its code

00:00:07.166 --> 00:00:10.200
like recognising a face polymorphic malware

00:00:10.200 --> 00:00:11.960
avoids this by changing how it looks

00:00:11.960 --> 00:00:13.300
each time it spreads

00:00:14.560 --> 00:00:18.320
the harmful part called the day lowest stays the same

00:00:18.320 --> 00:00:21.180
but it is hidden in a different way every time

00:00:21.800 --> 00:00:24.240
each version uses a new encryption key

00:00:24.240 --> 00:00:27.820
and include extra useless code in its decryption body

00:00:27.840 --> 00:00:30.400
to avoid desection because of this

00:00:30.400 --> 00:00:34.600
it's hash the digital fingerprints changes every time

00:00:34.600 --> 00:00:37.420
so antivirus program don't recognise it

00:00:46.960 --> 00:00:49.580
polymorphic Malware changes its appearance

00:00:49.600 --> 00:00:51.940
metamorphic Malware goes further

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:54.300
it through write its own code completely

00:00:54.300 --> 00:00:57.153
even though the code may look different

00:00:57.153 --> 00:00:59.073
it still does the same thing

00:00:59.073 --> 00:01:00.753
instructions may change

00:01:00.753 --> 00:01:04.053
names may change and extra lines may be added

00:01:04.073 --> 00:01:05.933
but the results stays the same

00:01:07.673 --> 00:01:09.233
that's what makes it dangerous

00:01:09.233 --> 00:01:12.773
it's hard to detect but it always causes the same harm

